title: $100k BBPA Racing Series - West Palm Beach
12 Hours of Pine Log 2011
course: 8 mile course with mixture of single and double track.
registration: You can register online at Active.com.
notes: Races start at 10 AM on Saturday, October 29th and will end at 10 PM that night.  12 & 6 hour race.  12 HR Co-Ed (4 people max), 12 HR Male Team and 12 HR Male and Female solo (12 lap min).  6 HR Team (2 people max), 6 HR Solo (6 lap min.) and 6 HR Singlespeed (6 lap min.).  3 deep payout for all categories.  $1650 for 12 HR coed and 12 HR solo racers.  USA Cycling rules apply for this event, and it is the responsibility of the rider to know the rules before starting the event.
directions: Pine Log State Forest, Ebro, Florida

title: Tally Cross
description: Tally Cross: 1st race in the 2011 Florida Cyclocross series and along with FSU we are also hosting collegiate races as well. Awesome prizes and $500 payout for Women\'s and Men\'s A races on both days.  So come join us for two days of Cyclocross action on the 5th and 6th of November at our new wide open course.
course: We are utilizing a new location for Tally cross this year at the Centerville Conservation Community.  This new location will enable us to provide all of the aspects of great Cyclocross racing: gravel roads, asphalt, and of course some steep grassy hills.
registration: Register online at USAcycling.org and of course we will have onsite registration on both race days.
directions:
8240 Centerville road Tallahassee, Fl 32309 
Follow the race signs when you reach the Centerville Conservation community.
